# 4 Carat Pear Shaped Diamond Ring: Prices, Settings & On Hand {{year}}

A 4 carat pear shaped diamond ring at Blue Nile starts at [$75,775 for a natural GIA G-VS1 Ideal stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26211394?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and [$7,657 for a lab grown IGI D-VVS1 Ideal stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27423995?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — a 90% gap between natural and lab grown at the 4ct tier. The 4 carat pear shaped diamond ring total ranges from $76,000–$130,000+ for natural with a setting, and $8,500–$22,000 for lab grown with a setting. This guide covers every dimension of the 4ct pear diamond ring: natural GIA pricing, lab grown IGI options, ring settings with prices, how the stone looks on hand, and the exact stone-and-setting combinations that produce the best 4ct pear ring at every budget.

The 4 carat pear shaped diamond ring exists in a category of its own. Only four GIA Ideal-cut natural pear diamonds at 4ct are available on Blue Nile at any given time — this is not inventory variation, it is geological and market rarity. At approximately 15×9.5mm face-up, a 4ct pear diamond covers nearly the full width of a finger — the tier where a pear ring stops being a statement piece and becomes an heirloom-class object.

## TL;DR: 4 Carat Pear Shaped Diamond Ring — What to Know

- **Natural GIA 4ct pear ring:** Stone [$75,775 G-VS1 GIA 4.01ct](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26211394?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — [$124,452 D-VS1 GIA 4.02ct](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28137271?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + setting. Ring total $76,500–$129,000+.
- **Lab grown 4ct pear ring:** Stone [$7,657 D-VVS1 IGI Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27423995?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + solitaire setting. Total ring ~$8,457. Lab grown D-IF at [$17,598](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28558318?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + platinum halo = $21,603 total.
- **Natural vs lab savings at 4ct:** $75,775 natural vs $7,657 lab at comparable grades — **90% savings** — an absolute dollar difference of $68,118 on the stone alone.
- **4ct pear on hand:** At ~15×9.5mm, a 4ct pear covers nearly the full width of most fingers, is unmistakably visible from 15+ feet, and registers as an extraordinary piece in every setting — formal or casual.
- **Ring settings for 4ct:** Solitaire (14K WG ~$800, platinum ~$1,500); [sidestone 14K YG $1,820](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pear-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-4-ct-tw-item-192877?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational); halo [14K WG $3,570](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pear-shape-side-stone-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-310842?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) or [platinum $4,005](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pear-shape-side-stone-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-310847?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). V-tip prong is mandatory at 4ct.
- **Contrarian Truth:** The [$75,775 GIA G-VS1 4.01ct](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26211394?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) costs $43,242 LESS than the [$119,017 D-VS1 4.01ct](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27638147?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) for the same carat weight and clarity at identical certification. The color difference between G and D is invisible to the naked eye in any ring setting. G-VS1 is the correct natural 4ct pear buy.
- **Priority:** → The [IGI D-VVS1 4ct lab pear at $7,657](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27423995?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + 14K WG solitaire at ~$800 = ring total ~$8,457. Natural buyers: the [$75,775 G-VS1 4.01ct](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26211394?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the only sub-$80K natural GIA 4ct pear at Blue Nile. See The Four-Stone Market analysis below.

## 4 Carat Pear Shaped Diamond Price: Natural GIA

Natural GIA-certified 4ct pear diamonds are among the rarest stones in Blue Nile's entire catalog. At the 1ct tier, Blue Nile carries 30+ natural GIA pear options; at 3ct, inventory narrows to four or five stones; at 4ct, Blue Nile typically carries exactly four natural GIA Ideal-cut pear diamonds total. This four-stone ceiling is not a restocking lag — it reflects the geological reality that round, clean, well-proportioned pear crystal formations at 4ct are extraordinarily rare in the natural diamond supply chain. For the full pear diamond inventory across all tiers, see the [Loose Pear Diamonds guide](/loose-pear-diamonds).

